content
=======
This directory contains 
1) the modified QUEST package: dqmc_tdmx
2) the modified Maximum Entropy Method code: MEM_xzx


Directory structure
===================
1) dqmc_tdmx
   SRC: source code for dqmc lib in which dqmc_tdxmRT.F90 is the F90 
        module for measuring chiKK and chiDD. Please find the related
        note: cvs-home/papers/linear_response_optical_lattice/note_v3.0.tex

   APPLY: applications, focus on using dqmc_tdmxRT.F90
          sub-directories are:
          a) parallel: 2D square lattice, parallel computing for non binned data
          b) parallel: 3D Cubic lattice, parallel computing for non binned data
          c) tdm_2d_mpi: 2D square lattice, parallel computing for binned data of
             time-dependent quantities 
          d) tdm_3d_mpi: 3D Cubic lattice, parallel computing for binned data of
             time-dependent quantities
          e) tdm: single process version for measuring time-dependent quantities

2) MEM_xzx
   BRYAN: the Bryan code by Mark
   readmc_tdmx: modified code of rddcams.f and readmc_linuxms.f for output by dqmc_tdmx
   readmc_w: modified code of rddcams.f and readmc_linuxms.f for MEM using 
             Matsubara frequency for spin chains
   readmc_e: modified code of rddcams.f and readmc_linuxms.f for MEM measuring specific heat
   sigma_w:  modified code of rddcams.f and readmc_linuxms.f for MEM using 
             Matsubara frequency for Greens' function
   path_use: shell script for path of MC data and output of MEM data
   onedqmc:  shell script for dqmc_tdmx MC data and output of MEM data
             usage: 
             a) start from default model:
                ...MEM$ ./onedqmc B4kkt B4kkt 1080 1 def
                where: B4kkt (first): index for output data
                       B4kkt (second): index for MC data
                       1080: number of data bins
                          1: coarse grain size
                        def: flag for using Gaussian default model
             b) annealing method
                ...MEM$ ./onedqmc B5ddt B4ddt 1080 1
                where: B5ddt (first): index for output data
                       B4ddt (second): index for MC data (input)
                       1080: number of data bins
                          1: coarse grain size
------------------------------------------------------------------------       
